article.description: Christina Wirth scored 21 points and Vanderbilt (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) routed Alabama 88-64 on Sunday.
article.headline: Wirth leads run to help No. 22 Vanderbilt put away Alabama
article.linkText: Wirth's 21 lead Vanderbilt's rout of Alabama
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Christina Wirth scored 21 points and Vanderbilt (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) routed Alabama 88-64 on Sunday.

Merideth Marsh added 17 points, hitting five 3-pointers for the Commodores (17-5, 6-1 Southeastern Conference). Chanel Chisholm had 10 points and Jence Rhoads had eight assists.

Wirth scored eight points during a 15-0 run that gave Vanderbilt the lead for good.

Varisia Raffington scored a career-high 27 points, including seven 3-pointers, to lead Alabama (12-10, 0-7). Tierney Jenkins added 18 points and a game-high 10 rebounds.

Alabama's last lead was at 15-14 after Jenkins' layup. The Tide got no closer than 18 in the second half.
